# React Native Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Use Expo for most projects (managed workflow), eject only when needed
- Use file-based routing with Expo Router
- Organize by features: `features/auth/`, `features/home/`
- Separate platform-specific code: `Component.ios.tsx`, `Component.android.tsx`

## Navigation (Expo Router)
- Use file-based routing in `app/` directory
- Use `<Stack>` for stack navigation, `<Tabs>` for tab navigation
- Use `useRouter()` for programmatic navigation
- Deep link support is automatic with Expo Router

## Performance
- Use `FlatList` for long lists (not `ScrollView` with `.map()`)
- Use `React.memo` for list items to prevent re-renders
- Use `useCallback` for event handlers passed as props
- Avoid inline styles — use `StyleSheet.create()`
- Use `Hermes` engine (default in Expo) for faster startup

## Styling
- Use `StyleSheet.create()` for type-safe, optimized styles
- Use `Dimensions` or `useWindowDimensions()` for responsive layouts
- Use NativeWind (Tailwind for RN) for utility-first styling
- Support both iOS and Android design conventions

## Native Modules
- Use Expo modules first (Camera, Location, Notifications)
- Use `expo-modules-core` for custom native modules
- Test on real devices, not just simulators
